 name from Coudrai in Seine-Maritime, France, or Coudray in Eure, France, or from Cowdray or Cowdry in Sussex, England. The latter was probably named after one of the places in France. All are named with Old French <i>coudraie</i> ‘hazel copse’ (a collective noun from <i>coudre</i> ‘hazelnut tree’, Late Latin <i>colurus</i>, a metathesized form of classical Latin <i>corylus</i>, from Greek <i>korylos</i>). Alternatively, but less likely, a topographic name from Old French <i>coudraie</i> ‘hazel copse’, adopted into English, denoting someone who lived near a hazel copse."]}]},{"name":"Catherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Catheryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["Greek: Same as Catherine."]},{"name":"Catharin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Catharine","meanings":["Greek: Pure."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Catherine De Cowdray was born about 1395, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Robert De Cowdray, was 102 and her mother, Eleanor De Cowdray, was 96. She married Sir Robert Otis Halsall about 1410. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1478, in Halsall, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 84."},"et":{"Abt 1395–1478":"umbes 1395–1478","1335–1378":"1335–1378","1395–1478":"1395–1478","–Female":"Surnud","1390–1420":"139